stored procedure vs. function
a. permanent environment change
Function can not do dml to a permananttable
but stored procedure can
b. input and output, parameters
function must have a input parameter and return a vaue(can be a scalar or result set)
sps don't have to take a parameter and don't not have a particular output
c. transactions
function don't not use transactions
d. call from each other
e. usage in select/where/having
Sproc can't do this
f. Try Catch block 
function can't do this
g. Temp table
function dont support temptable
h.dynamic sql
function don't support dynamic sql
